      "arguments": {
        "channel_id": "4rn5g95hrj5w0xnsq107djy9we",
        "title": "Q4 FY2024 Results: A Strong Finish to a Record Year",
        "body": "<h2>Q4 FY2024 Results: A Strong Finish</h2>\n<p>Apple today reported a solid finish to fiscal year 2024, underscoring the company\u2019s trajectory of durable growth and disciplined execution. For the September quarter, Apple posted revenue of <strong>$391.0B</strong>, up 2% year over year, reflecting solid performance across product and services. Gross margin stood at <strong>46.2%</strong>, with operating income of <strong>$123.2B</strong> and net income of <strong>$93.7B</strong>.</p>\n<p>Across segments, Services contributed approximately <strong>$96B</strong> in annual revenue, underscoring the company\u2019s expanding ecosystem. The results highlight ongoing demand for iPhone, Mac, iPad, Wearables, and Services as Apple continues to execute on its roadmap with a focus on privacy, on-device intelligence, and premium experiences.</p>\n<p>Apple\u2019s leadership reaffirmed a commitment to innovation and responsible growth, balancing investment in research and development with a disciplined capital-return program. The company remains focused on delivering products and services that customers love while maintaining a strong balance sheet and a clear path to long-term value creation.</p>\n<p>Read the full report at investor.apple.com.</p>",
